The paper deals with sampling and estimation of graph signals, which involves concepts from information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the use of greedy algorithms for sampling, which is a common technique in optimization (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI).
